The paper deals with the problem of preserving differential privacy using random projection matrices, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of random projections also has applications in machine learning and data analysis, which fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the run time of certain queries, which is a topic related to cryptography (cs.CR).
